    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-11-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-11-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="472"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d472">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.113/603</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moore</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-11-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 22, 1923</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received December 11.]</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 145</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to the Department’s unnumbered
                    Instruction of October 17th last,<note n="47" xml:id="d472fn47">See footnote 45,
                            <ref target="#pg_614">p. 614</ref>.</note> regarding the modification of
                    the terms of the existing embargo on the shipment of arms and munitions of war
                    to China, and directing me to ask whether the Spanish Government would instruct
                    its representative at Peking of its approval of the amended draft resolution and
                    the interpretative note, and of its readiness to give its formal assent thereto
                    upon there being substantial unanimity of action among the Powers represented at
                    Peking, I have the honor to report that I have been informed by the Foreign
                    Office, in a Note dated November 20th, that the Spanish Minister at Peking has
                    already been instructed in that sense.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alexander P. Moore</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
